The paper discusses a method for improving the implementation complexity of the Successive-Cancellation List (SCL) decoder for polar codes, which are commonly used in communication systems. This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, which is the most likely category. Additionally, the paper involves sorting algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), signal processing (cs.SI), computer architecture (cs.AR), and computational complexity (cs.CC), which are all relevant sub-categories.
